{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 678229, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Herecius", "body": "The ability 'rocket strike' is the first ability in WoW requiring SCIENTIFIC NOTATION to describe the damage.", "date": "2009-04-15T18:10:14-05:00", "rating": 129, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That unfortunately (?) is a bug, that's how it looks like when Blizzard messes up the tooltips, the damage in the tooltip of windfury weapon had similar notation after the release of patch 3.0, and wasn't fixed until a later patch.  They should keep the notation like that, and change the spell name to \"Rocket Science\".", "creationdate": "2009-04-16T06:29:28-05:00", "id": 91560, "rating": 33, "commentid": 678229, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "eikyu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually, that's engineering notation, which is even more appropriate.  V Proper scientific notation would be 5x10^6. Engineers use shorthands like 5E+6 or 5M.", "creationdate": "2009-04-20T16:21:06-05:00", "id": 92674, "rating": 50, "commentid": 678229, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "218667", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Unless I'm mistaken, http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=55336 is the first ability to require a scientific notation.", "creationdate": "2009-04-21T23:52:51-05:00", "id": 93024, "rating": 33, "commentid": 678229, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ryley", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Obviously you haven't seen [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44838]Slow-Roasted Turkey[/url]. All I know is that you gain some stamina and attack power.", "creationdate": "2009-09-10T06:28:39-05:00", "id": 121272, "rating": 30, "commentid": 678229, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "81147", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "alas, if only the e was euler's constant v_v", "creationdate": "2009-10-16T13:36:37-05:00", "id": 127667, "rating": 8, "commentid": 678229, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "311760", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 684380, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "353206", "body": "Currently during phase 4 of the fight, it is very common for the VX-001 (middle) and Flame Leviathan MkII (bottom) sections to cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63414]Spinning Up[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63631]Shock Blast [/url]simultaneously. Each is a 4 second cast and is handled in the same way as in phases 1 and 2, but the nature of this makes it the most challenging part of this phase. It requires your melee to run away from the boss while dodging mines and run away from wherever the Laser Barrage is pointed. Ranged dps have it notably easier here and may be prefered purely for this part of the fight.\n\nAlso in this event, your (Flame Leviathan) tank should generally charge back in after Shock Blast is cast to minimise any movement of the boss, while making sure to aim for a side that the barrage isn't being cast at, as it will lead to him being oneshot and everyone else shortly afterwards.\n\nSome players are claiming this is a bug, but it remains unconfirmed by Blizzard, so bad luck might be the answer.\n\n[EDIT] As of Patch 3.1.1 Mimiron can no longer cast Shock Blast and Laser Barrage at the same time in phase 4.", "date": "2009-04-19T07:35:17-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-14T04:40:19-05:00", 2, "353206"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 685790, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hayenne", "body": "Anyone thinks of Mimiron as of veiled reference to Tier5 raid content?\r\n\r\nPhase I is somewhat similar to Void Reaver (pounding; except you shouldn't dodge orbs as ranged dps)\r\nPhase II is Lurker Below\r\nPhase III is Lady Vashj (get the #@%! away from striders and nuke 'em!)\r\nPhase IV reminded me Kael'thas (You fight with each of his council members separately; then with all of them at time)", "date": "2009-04-20T06:23:17-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-20T07:12:04-05:00", 2, "Hayenne"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 685826, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Magnett", "body": "No one, sadly:\n\nRecent edit: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?achievement=4626]I was proven wrong![/url]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankIntro01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Oh, my! I wasn't expecting company! The workshop is such a mess! How embarrassing!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankHardIntro01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Now why would you go and do something like that? Didn't you see the sign that said DO NOT PUSH THIS BUTTON? How will we finish testing with the self-destruct mechanism active?\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankActive01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"We haven't much time, friends! You're going to help me test out my latest and greatest creation! Now, before you change your minds, remember that you kind of owe it to me after the mess you made with the XT-002!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankSlay01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"MEDIC!\" (possibly the best quote in the whole game)[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankSlay02.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"I can fix that. Erm, maybe not. Sheesh, what a mess!\" (I stand corrected.)[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TankDeath01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Wonderful! Positively marvelous results! Hull integrity at ninety-eight point nine percent! Barely a dent! Moving right along!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TorsoActive01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Behold, the VX-001 anti-personnel assault cannon! You might want to take cover...\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TorsoSlay01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Fascinating! I think they call that a clean kill!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TorsoSlay02.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Note to self: cannon highly effective against flesh!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_TorsoDeath01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Thank you, friends, your efforts have yielded some fantastic data! Now, where did I put... oh, there it is!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_HeadActive01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Isn't it beautiful? I call it the magnificent aerial command unit!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_HeadSlay01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Outplayed.\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_HeadSlay02.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"You can do better than that!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_HeadDeath01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Preliminary testing phase complete. Now comes the true test!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_Voltron01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Gaze upon its magnificence! Bask in its glorious... erm... glory! I present you with... V0-7TR-0N!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_VoltronSlay01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Prognosis negative!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_VoltronSlay02.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"You're not going to get up from that one, friend!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_Berserk01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"Oh, my! It would seem that we are out of time, my friends!\"[/i]\n\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Mimiron\\\\UR_Mimiron_VoltronDeath01.wav\")[/b]\n[i]\"It would appear that I made a slight miscalculation. I allowed my mind to be corrupted by that fiend in the prison! Over-riding my primary directive. All systems seem to be functional now. Clear.\"[/i]", "date": "2009-04-20T07:02:22-05:00", "rating": 48, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I wonder why the wowhead client does not have a sound at the end of an upload containing \"Thank you, friends, your efforts have yielded some fantastic data!\". It would be fitting in nicely.", "creationdate": "2017-02-09T23:52:24-06:00", "id": 1031560, "rating": 2, "commentid": 685826, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jazeera", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "replace .wav by .ogg", "creationdate": "2018-11-21T02:19:31-06:00", "id": 1205796, "rating": 0, "commentid": 685826, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "GeertJan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-09T12:23:26-05:00", 5, "Magnett"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 686365, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iconix", "body": "One thing that should be corrected in the description of the fight.  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63689]Plasma Ball[/url] used in phases 3 and 4 does not attack a random target.  This attack will be cast on the highest threat target and thus can be tanked by a ranged dps or healer.", "date": "2009-04-20T14:09:43-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 687254, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "CrulMighthammer", "body": "After being killed, an engineer can use his skill to \"engineer\" Mimiron's Body and get some loots from it.  Not sure about lowest skill req. to loot him, but my 450 did well. Remember to make screenshots first!\n\nFrom our first kilI got:\n- 1x Titansteel Bar\n- 6x Eternal Shadow\n- 5x Overcharged Capacitor. \n\nUpdating new kill 22.04 his body was \"engineered\" for following items:\n- 3x Eternal Fire\n- 3x Eternal Air\n- 3x Froststeel Tube\n- 15x Saronite Bar\n\nUpdating new kill 28.04, here what we got:\n- 1x Titansteel Bar\n- 4x Eternal Earth\n- 2x Eternal Fire\n- 9x Handful of Cobalt Bolts", "date": "2009-04-21T03:37:48-05:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-29T01:09:50-05:00", 3, "CrulMighthammer"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 688016, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "zapiks44", "body": "Widely considered one of the most difficult bosses in Ulduar, and after spending hours wiping to him last night, I can vouch for that. Some guilds refer to him as the \"Shade of Aran\" of Ulduar, and once you reach him, it'll be easy to see why.\r\n\r\nPhase 1 is mostly a tank-and-spank, just have melee run out of the Shock Blast and heal up whoever gets napalm'd. Also have abilities like Shield Wall, Pain Suppression, and Guardian Spirit ready to ensure your tank lives through Plasma Blast (use one of each of these for each blast).\r\n\r\nPhase 2 is VERY healing-intensive. This part is essentially a gear-check for your healers. They have to keep up a raid which will be taking massive damage from Bursts and Heat Waves. Also something of a retard-check to avoid the Laser Barrages and Rocket Strikes.\r\n\r\nPhase 3 is a similar gear-check for your DPS. Select a ranged DPS (preferably a demo-lock with Soul Link) to tank the ACU. Select another ranged DPS to \"kite\" the Assault Bots (preferably your highest-damage hunter) while the rest of your DPS kill them as fast as possible. It's also a good idea to have a rogue put Crippling Poison on their offhand and shiv the Assault Bots as quickly as possible, to keep it snared. In case you're wondering why they're kited, lets just say they hit our main tank for 60,000. After dying, the assault bots drop a magnetic core which can be used to bring down the head, stun it, and cause it to take additional damage. If you kill the Assault Bots fast enough, you'll have a good 10-15sec to burn the boss before the next Assault Bot spawns. The junk bots can be easily tanked and AOEed once the phase is over.\r\n\r\nPhase 4 is basically a combination of all three previous phases, so as you could imagine, it's quite hectic. Split up your DPS among each of the three parts of the machine, while everyone keeps a close eye on the health of all three parts to ensure they will all die within seconds of each other. Whoever tanked the head phase 3 should do so again here. This part is partially luck-based (a Laser Barrage and Shock Blast at once will almost certainly kill some of your melee) and requires everyone to be very observant of when a Laser Barrage or Shock Blast is coming, which are the most dangerous parts of this phase. Stay calm, stay focused, and you'll get him down.", "date": "2009-04-21T14:13:53-05:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "There's no need for kiting on Phase 3. You already have a tank to do it's job, besides they apply a debuff which immobilizes the tank. So kiting is impossible on Phase 3.", "creationdate": "2009-05-09T18:33:06-05:00", "id": 404984, "rating": 3, "commentid": 688016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "228172", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
