{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 694646, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "114759", "body": "In comparison with the other 3 keeper bosses (Hodir, Thorim, Freya), this boss is extremely difficult. It took my guild upwards of 12 hours of attempts to down him on 10-man. Here is some advice:\r\n\r\nThis is not the most melee friendly fight. Although you can certainly do it with a good amount of melee, it seems to go smoother if you only have one or two. We tried this boss with multiple group set-ups; here is the one we killed him with.\r\n\r\nFeral Druid (Tank)\r\n\r\nBoomkin, Hunter, Hunter, Mage, Warlock (Ranged DPS)\r\n\r\nEnhance Shaman (Melee DPS)\r\n\r\nHoly Pally, Resto Druid, Holy Priest (Healers)\r\n\r\nThe composition on this boss is flexible; no specific classes are needed. Although it may be possible to 2-heal this boss, we were unable to do so because of the plasma blasts in phase 1. \r\n\r\nThe most important thing to consider when selecting people for this fight is awareness. The challenge of this fight is avoiding the many ways you can die if you are not completely focused. With that in mind, it will take a while before your group members will get good at this fight. You'll probably wipe a lot on the first three phases before you get them perfect. Patience is key; repeated deaths on the same mechanic, however, should raise some eyebrows.\r\n\r\nIn phase 1, have your ranged DPS and healers spread out on one side of the boss. Once they have a spot they don't have to move for the rest of the phase. The boss will shoot a fire ball at one person that will put a DOT on them and they have to be healed through it. The boss does an ability called Plasma Blast that hits the main tank for 17,600 damage per second unmitigated for 5 seconds. The tank must be spam healed through this. A cooldown rotation is highly recommended for both the tank's cooldowns and any other mitigation cooldowns in the raid, such as Divine Guardian. With proper DPS you should only get 2 or 3 plasma blasts.\r\n\r\nHere is an example cooldown rotation for a feral tank's abilities: First blast barkskin. Second blast survival instincts and frenzied regeneration. Third blast barkskin.\r\n\r\nOther than that, the main raid killer in this phase is the boss's shock blast and mines. After each plasma blast (sometimes during a plasma blast if you have high DPS), the boss will do a shock blast. You can see him casting this ability, and when he does melee and the tank have to run away from him. The ability is an AOE that will one-shot anyone who doesn't run. It does less damage the further you run. The range is relatively small, only about 15 yards, so as long as you run you should live. While running out make sure you run through a gap in the mines surrounding the boss (he throws mines in a circle around him periodically). Although one mine is not life-threatening, two or more can kill you.\r\n\r\nYou can charge back in after the shock blast, but be aware that charge pathing can run you through mines if you aren't careful. If the run distance and timing are executed perfectly, a warrior or feral druid tank can keep the boss from moving when they charge back in.\r\n\r\nAt the beginning of phase two, stay away from leftover mines; don't worry, they will explode by the start of the phase. Also, do not stand on the circle in the middle of the room; you will get thrown back when the floor opens up. On this phase the boss is untankable and will shoot a conal attack directed at one person. The conal attack will also hit anyone else near the person so ranged need to spread out. Melee DPS should continually run behind the boss each time he turns. The boss will also do an ability called Laser Barrage which follows the cast 'spinning up'. Similar to The Lurker Below's spout attack, anyone caught in front of the boss during this ability will be killed almost instantly; it deals about 18k damage every 0.5 seconds. his ability only goes 180 degrees and only goes in the direction the boss span up, so just run behind him. Melee should be careful not to stand too far into the boss's center or the barrage may clip them.\r\n\r\nThs boss will also shoot a rocket off his back. If you are the target of the rocket a flashing red circle will appear beneath your feet. You must run out of the circle or you will be one-shotted.\r\n\r\nIn phase 3, you will fight an aerial unit. A ranged DPS must tank this (we used a warlock). On this phase the tank should be picking up assault bots (which spawn from orange beams of light) and junk bots (which spawn from green beams of light). Assault bots will one-shot a non-tank so it is crucial that they are picked up ASAP; junk bots do not hit hard so if one is loose it is not a priority until assault bots are secured. All melee DPS should be on these bots while the command unit is in the air. Assault bots can be stunned, and will also do a channeled spell 'magnetic pull' that stuns the tank. This is interruptable.\r\n\r\nAssault bots drop an item called magnetic core (like the cores on Lady Vashj). One person should be assigned to pick these up and put them below the boss. This will pull the boss onto the ground; everybody should DPS him during this time. \r\n\r\nAll ranged should have a macro '/target Bomb Bot'. Bomb bots will spawn throughout this phase; they run very fast and will likely kill anyone they get to. Ranged must target them as soon as the bots drop through the air. They should be dead within a few seconds of hitting the ground so that they don't get near anybody; if a bomb bot is coming toward you run away. Assault and junk bots should be tanked away from where bomb bots land to avoid melee being blown up.\r\n\r\nAfter the command unit is down, kill any remaining bots and get into position (ranged spread out). The three machines will now combine and maintain some of their previous abilities. The bottom will still throw mines and shock blast, the middle will still do a conal attack, rockets, and laser barrage, and the top will still shoot plasma balls at its primary target. Each unit starts at 50% health . Melee are only capable of attacking the bottom and middle. All of these parts must be killed within 5 seconds of each other or they will self-repair. \r\n\r\nThe most challenging part of this phase is the laser barrage. With everything else going on it is easy for ranged and healers to not notice the barrage quickly enough and be caught in it; it can also be difficult to get away in time if the barrage faces directly at you. Everybody must remain aware for this phase. You must continue to avoid mines, shock blast, rockets, and laser barrage, while spreading out for the conal attack and paying attention to health %s as you burn the three parts down.\r\n\r\nTanking is very sensitive during this phase. It is important to move the boss as little as possible, and to reposition quickly after shock blast. Note that the boss can do shock blast and laser barrage right after each other; this is difficult to handle. During the laser barrage the bottom of the boss can be turned seperately from the middle so that the tank can avoid being hit.\r\n\r\nJust keep your cool and stay alive. The better your raid gets at living the sooner you will down this boss.\r\n\r\nBest of luck.", "date": "2009-04-26T09:11:20-05:00", "rating": 35, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "My group has been using this strategy (more or less) for 2 weeks now and we're able to survive until mana becomes a problem (which is usually after failing several times to kill all 3 parts at the same time in phase 4).  So even having learned how to stay alive and manage mana pools it's still a huge pain to get those parts down all at once.  Can anyone confirm what the time is? Some posts here say 5 sec, some say 15 sec and my guild leader was under the impression that it was 10 sec. personally I think it should be a little longer in 10 man then it is in 25 man.  Any tips in this regard would", "creationdate": "2009-04-26T09:11:21-05:00", "id": 404079, "rating": 3, "commentid": 694646, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "223653", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I believe it is 10 seconds. One way to get all the parts dead at the same time is to DPS them all down to 20% (call DPS off on a part when it reaches 20% until all parts are that low). Then burn them to 10%, then 5%, then kill them (Make sure DPS are assigned to each part). This is what worked for us.   If you are surviving in phase 4 for that long then the hard part is already over for you. Just make sure your DPS is coordinated and you've got it.", "creationdate": "2009-05-05T20:40:03-05:00", "id": 96198, "rating": 8, "commentid": 694646, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "114759", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-05T20:50:25-05:00", 3, "114759"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 695778, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "cangiz", "body": "I dont know about you guys, but my guild has been stuck on phase 4 of Mimiron for the last week. Try as we may our efforts are thwarted. When messing around like i do best, I found that you can actually apply [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44228]Baby Spice[/url] to the lower body of the Machine in P4 and make the Head attackable by melee. This can help greatly with keeping everything within the 15 second kill range. I havent been able to take screen shots but its a pretty easy concept to understand. \r\n\r\nThanks , hope it helps you out.", "date": "2009-04-27T03:12:25-05:00", "rating": 53, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Baby Spice can also be used on Mimiron in Phase 2, making rocket strikes on melee FAR more visible and moving behind him (out of turret fire) easier.  Note: This was before Baby Spice was \"fix't\" to no longer effect bosses.", "creationdate": "2009-05-20T15:06:01-05:00", "id": 99131, "rating": 14, "commentid": 695778, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MarioMetroid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 696900, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "295481", "body": "As of the latest patch, the P3Wx2 Laser Barrage in phase 4 will now go at the usual speed. On some raids, the laser will spin at one rotation per second. This is a glitch that wiped many raids.", "date": "2009-04-27T22:51:55-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 696990, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "321041", "body": "You can bug it out to reset it if you have a warlock. Get them to put their demonic circle up at the roaming boomers outside the boss room, and if the tank dies/raid starts to wipe etc you can have him recall, and once the boss makes it down the agro charts to him he will run through the wall and reset the fight.\nIt's not a foolproof safety net because anyone with higher threat will get pulped, (and random raid members will get hit by phase specific skills such as napalm) but it can usually save a healer or, in the very least, some repair monies.", "date": "2009-04-28T01:02:44-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-28T01:14:26-05:00", 1, "321041"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 697218, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rommel88mm", "body": "After reading some of the strats on this boss, i wanted to put in my own lil helping comment.  On the 3rd phase, we found a very easy way to get through it was to have a high health individual that can taunt, who wasnt the MT, to stand near Mimiron to wait for the bomb bots to drop out.  He then taunted it and just took the dmg.  Doing that ment we could just all group up and deal with the adds/dps the boss unhindered.  It works for out 10 man, not sure if it holds true in 25man", "date": "2009-04-28T06:21:52-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It's about 20k on heroic, we had a Shaman's Fire elemental placed under him with an OT standing by", "creationdate": "2009-04-28T14:41:52-05:00", "id": 402813, "rating": 3, "commentid": 697218, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Calidus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you have a DK you can Chains of Ice them (twice if you have to, the first rune will be reactive by the time the next bomb comes down). This was tested on 10 man. I don't know if they spawn faster in 25  Also if you have no DK, druid tanks can easily eat the damage due to their high health.", "creationdate": "2009-04-28T15:08:30-05:00", "id": 94598, "rating": 3, "commentid": 697218, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "321041", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The fire elemental will not stay under Mimiron, and even when it hugs under mimiron I've yet to see the bomb blow up on it.", "creationdate": "2009-06-04T23:08:17-05:00", "id": 102016, "rating": 1, "commentid": 697218, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Orcao", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 697727, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "321041", "body": "This fight can be bugged out and reset if you have a warlock. Get them to put their demonic circle up at the edge of the ring of roaming boomers outside the boss room, and if the tank dies/raid starts to wipe etc you can have him recall. Once the boss makes it down the agro charts to the lock he (the boss) will run through the forcefield wall and reset the fight.\r\nIt's not a foolproof safety net because anyone with higher threat will get pulped, (and random raid members will get hit by phase specific skills such as MKII's Napalm Shell) but it can usually save a healer or, in the very least, some repair monies for anyone with lower threat than the warlock.", "date": "2009-04-28T15:02:18-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-28T15:05:18-05:00", 8, "321041"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 698128, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "FinestHour", "body": "does anyone have any tips for avoiding the missles during phase 2 for melee? when the boss is using heat wave its really difficult to see the mark on the ground that indicates the missle is going to land on a melee dps. we only get by from sheer luck i think...", "date": "2009-04-28T23:59:11-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tilt your camera so it's right above you and the boss. Now, when you see a rocket launch, you'll immediately see it tilt in one direction as it flies up and goes away from vertical path. Just don't stand in that possible line of fire and you should be gold", "creationdate": "2009-04-29T01:55:57-05:00", "id": 402898, "rating": 3, "commentid": 698128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Liquoid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Whoever is DPSing middle part, tell them that they should warn the raid when a missile launches, so that everyone can check whatever below them and move away.", "creationdate": "2009-05-09T18:40:16-05:00", "id": 96984, "rating": 6, "commentid": 698128, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "228172", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 698274, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "310530", "body": "I am having problem at p4 tanking\nkept dying to laser barrage even tho i am behind the target very weird\nthe thing is when u tank him and try to avoid laser barrage and he moves with u is annoying = =", "date": "2009-04-29T03:18:40-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "We had that problem for a while when we were trying to down him; with our melee tank (MkII tank) dying from Laser Barrage. After a couple of wipes on the fourth phase, we found out that indeed the tank has to turn the lower body but he has to do it very precisely.  Instead of just running behind, the tank has to carefully point him in another direction without moving him from the spot. Usually just running behind him makes him move for a couple of yards, which can sometimes make the middle part turn and rip your raid to shreds with Laser Barrage. Mimiron is almost all about perfection, especia", "creationdate": "2009-04-29T03:18:41-05:00", "id": 402958, "rating": 2, "commentid": 698274, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "353855", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-29T05:04:54-05:00", 2, "310530"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 698697, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hayenne", "body": "Prot warrior can actually tank p3 with ease. Just taunt+[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=64382]attract[/url] Head, then use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=23920]spell reflection[/url].\r\n\r\nYou will immediately get around 30k threat. Since ranged dps will concentrate on assault bots very soon, you can get some more reflections so threat will not be a problem even once he lands.", "date": "2009-04-29T12:07:00-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Didn't get a kill yet, but I was also able to tank this as a melee class in Phase 3 (dps Frost DK) in 10 man since our only ranged in the group had logged off earlier for the night.  I just popped Frost Presence, kept hitting the vehicle with Howling Blasts, dodged around the bomb bots as they spawned, and used cooldowns as necessary to easy up on the healing required.", "creationdate": "2009-04-30T14:11:14-05:00", "id": 94992, "rating": 5, "commentid": 698697, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dactyl", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 700882, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lillbrorsan", "body": "Major changes to several bosses in 3.1.2, here are the Mimiron changes.\r\n\r\n[quote]    * Proximity Mines now deals 15000 Fire damage. (Down from 25000 damage)\r\n\r\n    * Emergency Mode (Hard Mode) now increases damage and health by 30%. (Up from 25%)[/quote]", "date": "2009-05-01T05:17:35-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 703239, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "166696", "body": "For 10 man I found it worthwhile to just have 1 tank wearing a set just focused on health. 60% of the damage you eat is magical and comes in hughe bursts (p1) your armor, mitigation and avoidance dont help at all. This also helps finishing phase 1 to 3 a lot faster.\n\nAs a druid with around 48k hp buffed, I was completly self-reliable with my 3 cooldowns (Barkskin for the 1st and 3rd, survival instincts (last stand equivalent w/ glyph) for 2nd, and frenzied regeneration / heal pot for the 4th)\n\nP 1-3 seemed easy, at least with our 3-healer setup, but p4 turned out to be just a nightmare for me as a tank. The rockets land so quickly that calling them out over vent wasnt providing enough time to react and I didnt have enough oversight to do all the things I needed to do (dodging shockblast, finding holes in the minefield, positioning the boss correctly and my roatation) while watching the back of the boss for rocket launches at the same time.\n\nOnce we started using baby spice to shrink the lower part, I was able to see the target circle of the rockets and we downed the boss on the 2nd attempt.", "date": "2009-05-02T23:58:57-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-02T23:59:38-05:00", 1, "166696"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 704504, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nimbonya", "body": "Just to give this a little added boost, there's an easy method for dealing with the bombs that would only require minimal extra coordination from the raid as a whole. \r\n\r\n[quote]/target bomb\r\n/cast [Instant damaging spell]\r\n/targetlasttarget[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis macro when used effectivly shoots the chosen spell at any Bomb bots that are nearby, the targetlasttarget line resets your target to who or what you were previously targeting so quick its as if you never lost target in the first place. This can be used by DPS, Tanks and Healers alike with any form of instant ranged attack. Get your raid used to mashing this button a few times when someone over vent calls out the bomb spawn and Boom, no more bomb.", "date": "2009-05-03T22:37:57-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 705540, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nethris", "body": "Note for melee on phase 4:\r\n\r\nDo not, I repeat, DO NOT turn your camera up high to get a clearer view of the mines while in p4 if you are having trouble seeing them with the boss twisting around too much. The construction thingie on the roof does not clip your camera and you will be basically blind if your camera distance is set far away enough.\r\n\r\nLearned the hard when trying to move away from shock blast and didnt take a close enough look at mines beforehand :Z", "date": "2009-05-04T18:37:28-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 706783, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "146076", "body": "One thing I noticed today whilst attempting the 10-man version that I've yet to see mentioned elsewhere is that on the phase 3 to phase 4 transition, as you kill the remaining Assault Bot(s), you can actually loot their Cores still and hold onto them.\r\n\r\nUpon phase 4 starting simply dropping the Core underneath V0-L7R-0N causes the Head to take 50% extra damage. This greatly helps with the DPS burn required to get through this last phase quickly.", "date": "2009-05-05T19:29:15-05:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Can this be confirmed?", "creationdate": "2009-05-19T08:40:38-05:00", "id": 406663, "rating": 5, "commentid": 706783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "235006", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed.  As of 3.2, this no longer works.", "creationdate": "2009-05-25T00:09:44-05:00", "id": 99931, "rating": 15, "commentid": 706783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "cangiz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed - they last 1 minute so you can gather up 2 and drop them consecutively.  Trying to gather up 3 could be cutting it a bit fine.  We tried consecutive cores last night to prevent Mimiron from releasing more bomb bots but we weren't quite fast enough with the click-target-click.  I think it would be possible to prevent bots in this way if you're fast enough.", "creationdate": "2009-05-29T17:52:25-05:00", "id": 408445, "rating": 3, "commentid": 706783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "379641", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can no longer use Baby Spices on the bottom part nor can you use the cores on the head in phase 4.", "creationdate": "2009-08-14T08:55:08-05:00", "id": 116050, "rating": 9, "commentid": 706783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kepsen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Does this still work in 3.2?", "creationdate": "2009-08-17T14:19:54-05:00", "id": 420923, "rating": -1, "commentid": 706783, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "313096", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 707762, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "90775", "body": "The Archivum Data Disc provides the following insights when the quest is turned in:\r\n\r\nWatcher Mimiron's sigil is linked to a self-destruct mechanism connected to the entirety of the Corridors of Ingenuity.\r\nTrigger for self-destruct mechanism is codenamed \"Big Red Button\", Mimiron's own creation.\r\nTo retrieve Mimiron's sigil, initiate self-destruct sequence and defeat mimiron before its completion.", "date": "2009-05-06T16:41:11-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 709895, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "353420", "body": "Little known fact is that Mimiron has an aura active while hes starting up the Leviathan MK II\r\n\r\nBig Red Button - 100 yard aura that draws nearby players towards the button. Partially resistible; players without resistance must be yelled at not to do push it or the hard mode will activate", "date": "2009-05-08T17:37:01-05:00", "rating": 57, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 714695, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "354232", "body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=40081]Potion of Nightmares[/url] is extremely useful for healers between the phases. Use before or after phase 2.", "date": "2009-05-13T05:29:35-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 718594, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "367267", "body": "My guild was without a warlock, stuck on mimiron, for lack of a head tank that could hold aggro and stay alive reliably. Then while playing with my talent spec (im a mage) i found a ungodly strong combo for a tank..\nThe setup equires a disc priest, and mage in enough resist gear to give around 310 arcane and fire resistance (when adding talents and buffs), but have your arcane resist slighty higher, can be done with rings cloak and belt and the spec below while using mage armor.\n\n[url=http://www.wowarmory.com/talent-calc.xml?cid=8&tal=03502103012003015330313250532103000000000000000000000000002030230010000000000000000000]Tanking Build[/url]\n\n\nphase 1 and 2, the mage will be doing pretty dismal damage, but once he starts tanking, have the disc priest healing / shielding him, his sp will go thru the roof (i was at ~3500sp 90% of the time) and I had around 40-50% mitigation.\n\n[s]now for the reason for higher arcane resist, this is speculation, testing it next week, while shielded, have fire ward up with the \"frost warding\" talent. If you are familiar with the mage spell 'frosfire' you will know it does whichever damage type is resisted less. If spellfire works the same (which it appears to) it should trip the fire ward. Your ward is the last to go in shield order, it becomes a free 5-10k mana or more, every 30 sec, making a arcane blast spam at high spellpower be a viable attack pattern.\n[/s]\nThe base setup works like a dream, the last section, not sure about, feel free to try it out, its fun =D\n\nedit: tested the mana regen with fire ward, it dosn't seem to work, so keep ur arcane and ur fire resist as even as possible.", "date": "2009-05-17T03:37:59-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Shinyuu, I'd like to discuss this with you a bit more - looking for specifically which gear you're using/enchants/etc and how much unbuffed resist you have on each.  Spec looks almost exactly like my pvp spec so I'm pretty familiar.", "creationdate": "2009-05-25T21:15:13-05:00", "id": 100111, "rating": 1, "commentid": 718594, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "373299", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-25T21:04:11-05:00", 3, "367267"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 723351, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "106166", "body": "Now, for some mathematics for those of us who are ranged DPS or healers in phase 2 and believe that standing closer to the boss than in phase 1 (Where mines would make standing close equal a bad thing.) doesn't provide any benefit.\r\n\r\nIn phase 2, his turret will randomly target a person and do a frontal cone AoE attack to people who are close to his target. The cone type attack means that the width of the attack increases the further away you stand, but the angle remains the same. Now, all the possible ways it can turn is 360 degrees, but it fires in an angle of X degrees. Standing close means that the width is smaller due to the radius R in the formula for cone width (X/360)*pi*R^2 being smaller. The same amount of people will get hit, since everyone's standing still at a given angle anyway.\r\n\r\nThis formula goes for the P3Wx2 cannon attack as well, which rotates Y degrees, but requires you to run away from it, making a small distance desirable. \r\n\r\nStanding far away (A large R in the formula) means that the distance you have to run is a lot larger. You have to move the same amount of degrees anyway, but whereas the angle is constant, the radius increases with distance. Doubling your distance from the boss means that the distance you have to run to avoid the attack is quadrupled, meaning that even though you might get around the boss and spend half the duration of the beam attacks unloading those incredible Fireball crits if you stand close to the boss, and might not even outrun the beam at all if you stand close to the walls in the room.", "date": "2009-05-21T14:05:41-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "TLDR: Ranged dps and heals should stay close to boss in P2, as there is less to run.", "creationdate": "2009-05-25T20:34:39-05:00", "id": 100101, "rating": 8, "commentid": 723351, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "barbeque", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 723554, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "apatuka", "body": "V0-L7R-0N if you know on haxor speak the \"7\" its a \"L\" and \"0\" its a O.\r\n\r\nso u got this: VO-LTR-ON\r\n\r\njoining this in one without the \"-\" u got: Voltron, its so epic how blizzard put funny names on those bosses.\r\n\r\nVoltron was a TV series where vehicles joins together to transform it onto Voltron.\r\n\r\nV0-L7R-0N is a fusion between all Mimiron's machines like Voltron is.", "date": "2009-05-21T18:01:18-05:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Actually, '7' is supposed to be a 'T', not an 'L'", "creationdate": "2009-06-07T12:52:19-05:00", "id": 102455, "rating": 6, "commentid": 723554, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "336631", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "...1337?Quite obvious if you ask me..", "creationdate": "2009-06-08T05:33:59-05:00", "id": 102585, "rating": 7, "commentid": 723554, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "stathisdjs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 724289, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mahtamori", "body": "I can't for the life of me figure out why all guides say you should kite the Assault Bots in phase 3. They're perfectly tankable in 25 man, just don't get hit right after they spawn.", "date": "2009-05-22T12:52:54-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As long as dispellers instantly remove the debuff they give its very doable.", "creationdate": "2009-05-24T04:46:57-05:00", "id": 99766, "rating": 3, "commentid": 724289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "darkkeijp", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I'm 100% positive that somewhere after 3.1 they put a sneak nerf to assault bots. At your first attempts on Mimiorn they we're oneshotting the OT. Couple weeks later they were hitting for less than the old 10-man versions.  The assault bots cast somekind of channeled spell, magnetic field or somethig, which needs to be interrupted, or the OT might be in trouble.  On a side note, possibly the most fun boss I've ever killed.", "creationdate": "2009-05-25T04:40:25-05:00", "id": 99958, "rating": 5, "commentid": 724289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "129046", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 724791, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "95950", "body": "I'll contribute a link to the [url=http://mirrorshield.blogspot.com/2009/05/yakras-mimiron-tanking-guide.html]strat I wrote[/url] for Mimiron-25, which my guild has used successfully to down Mimiron. It covers everything, with a tank focus - and has a [url=http://hotstree.blogspot.com/2009/05/mimiron-healing-guide-with-healing.html]companion guide for healing[/url].", "date": "2009-05-23T00:50:16-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 727796, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wani", "body": "For the lore side of things, this guy was the Grand Architect who created the gnome race. All gnomes were mechagnomes before the Curse of Flesh hit them. One of the first gnomes created was [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=25834]Gearmaster Mechazod[/url], who was sent to Borean Tundra to \"fix\" the gnomes of the current age.\r\n\r\nAll in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=11708]this quest[/url], or something.", "date": "2009-05-26T02:52:24-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 735218, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ambracaos", "body": "Patch [url=http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/patchnotes/]3.1.3[/url] will be altering a few aspects of the Mimiron encounter.\r\n\r\n- His [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63041]Rocket Strikes[/url] have a longer flight time and prefer players standing at range.\r\n\r\n- During Phase 4 when [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33651]VX-001[/url] casts [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63300]Laser Barrage[/url] the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33432]Leviathan Mk II[/url] will be stunned.\r\n\r\n- His [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63016]Proximity Mines[/url] now will do less damage and have a lower duration, as well as a newly installed arming time so that they can no longer detonate immediately upon creation.", "date": "2009-06-02T14:29:23-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
