{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 746311, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "96968", "body": "I'm surprised no one has mentioned yet - Mimiron could very well be a reference to the Norse figure [url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M%C3%ADmir]Mimir[/url], much as you have Hodir from Odin, Thorim from Thor, and Freya from Freyr (and Loken from Loki). Like Mimiron he was supposed to be some wise and intelligent figure, though sadly not a mechano-gnome. He was decapitated and Odin took his head, not to make his own V0-L7R-0N to defend himself but rather to use it for advice and counsel.", "date": "2009-06-14T06:23:52-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Amusingly, the 4 Keepers were all originally designed as Greek Gods (Descendants of the Titans).  Instead of Thorim = Thor, Hodir = Odin, Mimiron = Mimir, and Freya, it likely would have been variants of Zues (God of Thunder, and his wife Hera instead of Sif), Boreas (god of the northern wind, and where we get the name for Borean Tundra), Haephestus (Smith God), and either Demeter (Earth and Fertility) Artemis (Wild Hunt) or Persephone (Fertility and Nature) as the Life Keeper.  One indicator of this is that Loken was originally named Chronus during the Beta Testing (and still is according to ", "creationdate": "2009-06-14T06:23:53-05:00", "id": 414688, "rating": 2, "commentid": 746311, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "272760", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This is almost completely certain.  A few quests concerning Brann Bronzebeard in Storm Peaks refer to Mimiron as Mimir, and even Archivist Mechaton is saying \"Keeper Mimir\" instead of Mimiron. I suppose this is a mistake on Blizzard's side, having forgotten to add the 'on' from those quests, or maybe he just thought it'd be funny to add a few more letters to his own name when the other Keepers went \"insane\"", "creationdate": "2009-06-27T11:47:49-05:00", "id": 412872, "rating": 0, "commentid": 746311, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "336631", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Further evidence: [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63796]Mimiron's Head[/url]", "creationdate": "2009-07-13T12:14:27-05:00", "id": 109481, "rating": 2, "commentid": 746311, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "28864", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 753978, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gutenlock", "body": "If you start hardmode once, can you choose to not go for hardmode another time? Had fun pulling him and then circle teleported out to see some great killing sprees, and wanted to try to start hardmode, but I didn't dare becuse maybe he would be stuck on enrage.", "date": "2009-06-21T16:28:47-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You have to press the button every time to activate hard mode. So feel free to use it to wipe your raid.", "creationdate": "2009-07-01T07:36:27-05:00", "id": 107077, "rating": 3, "commentid": 753978, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Matti", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-21T16:31:01-05:00", 1, "Gutenlock"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 756299, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "20675", "body": "And, in case anyone wants to know, here is the several computer countdown voice from the hardmode:\r\n\r\n[i]Self destruct sequence initiated![/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSDStart01.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 10 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD10.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 9 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD09.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 8 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD08.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 7 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD07.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 6 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD06.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 5 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD05.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 4 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD04.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 3 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD03.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 2 minutes.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD02.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]This area will self destruct in 1 minute.[/i]\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD01.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Self destruct sequence finallized. Have a nice day![/i] (If the boss enrages to the timer)\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSD00.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\n[i]Self destruct sequence finallized. override code A905.[/i] (If you kill him before the enrage)\r\n[b]/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\ArchivumSystem\\\\UR_Archivum_MimironSDEnd01.wav\")[/b]\r\n\r\nEnjoy! They certanly sound imba!", "date": "2009-06-23T16:29:56-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The 'Self destruct sequence finallized. Have a nice day!' could be a reference to the [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ulKwhhFOkgk]self-destruct sequence of Spaceballs[/url], where this phrase is more or less the same :D", "creationdate": "2010-03-25T20:28:53-05:00", "id": 155775, "rating": 1, "commentid": 756299, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 768, "username": "Merylyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
