{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 864977, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "savagehippie", "body": "Fought him for the first time last night in 10-man, and all I gotta say is come prepared, because this is one tough fight.  Each phase seems to get progressively more difficult, which the 4th and final phase being the hardest.\r\n\r\nOur group made the mistake of not bringing enough caster DPS along for the fight, so they could not keep up with our melee.  The first 3 phases actually aren't that bad, but be very careful of the bombs he drops in phase 3.  Raid warning macros will come very effective here, especially if you're the tank or melee DPS and are grouped up with all the trash adds that spawn, as you won't always necessarily know where the bombs are.  Once you're past that, the whole trick is assigning DPS roles to the 3 different parts of Mimiron in phase 4 to ensure that he is defeated properly.", "date": "2009-10-12T10:15:08-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
