{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 999433, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "561672", "body": "Mimer, Mimir, Mim - Are all old nordic names for the god of same name. Suffered the fate of being beheaded in the \u00c6sir / Vanir war, condemned to be carried around as only a living head (he is a god after all) by his good friend Odin, the \u00c6sir Val-father, top god of the Norse Mythology Pantheon. In this form he advice and cites secret knowledge to Odin.\r\n\r\nMaybe Mimir (the head) is inside this mechanical pest? Who knows what Blizz have been thinking and planning, using that name :)) It would suite fine that he knows Rocket Science...Thats secret knowledge or what for a mythology used in a time where the wheel was somewhat advanced.", "date": "2010-03-17T13:27:18-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
