{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 1119471, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sunlar", "body": "From my experience this is one of the hardest Hard Modes I have ever encountered.The tactics are not overly complicated, but you cannot possibly overlook them. Even if you overgear this fight, everyone must play according to the tactics, because if one player fails, that soon becomes a raid-wide mistake. Furthermore, it is crucial that no one dies over the course of the fight. Every raid member will be an important asset if you hope to beat this Hard Mode. \n\nMost will already know, but to activate this Hard Mode you need to push the [url=http://www.examiner.com/images/blog/EXID26051/images/MIM%282%29.jpg]big red button[/url] in Mimiron's room. After wiping quite a few times, my group came up with a strategy. I haven't read many guides on this fight, so this is my contribution for anyone who wishes to get the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=3180]Firefighter[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2957]Meta Achievement[/url]. In each phase section I will provide a description of what you will be up against, how to deal with it, and also a small separate explanation of the boss' abilities during each phase.\n\n[b]IMPORTANT:[/b] In between phases your group should stack at an assigned player near the wall, so that the fires will go to the back of the room and don't occupy precious space. Also, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=48947]Fire Resistance Aura[/url] is gold here.\n\n[b][u]Phase 1[/u][/b]:\n\nDuring this phase Mimiron will be on a vehicle, the Leviathan Mk. This is the easiest of the four phases. We had two tanks, one Warrior and one DK. This made it much easier for the healers because since we didn't have a Druid tank. We had the OT taunt the boss when the MT was afflicted by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=62997]Plasma Blast[/url]. Overall, ranged dps & the healers stayed close (with 6 yards between each other) and kept moving clockwise as the fire followed in their trail. It is wise to stay as close to the wall as possible so that the tanks have more space to move in case the middle is overrun with fire.\n\n[ul]\n[li]Abilities:[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63631]Shock Blast[/url]][u][/u][/b] > This ability takes 5 seconds to cast, and should ALWAYS be avoided by running away from the boss. If your tank(s) and melee get hit by this they will die. Warrior tanks can make good use of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=3411]Intervene[/url] to avoid it.\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=64529]Plasma Blast[/url]][s][/s][/b] > Everytime the boss uses this ability on the MT, the OT should taunt him or the MT will take an immense amount of damage. Cooldowns such as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=6940]Hand of Sacrifice[/url] are also helpful to lessen the amount of damage the tank takes from the Plasma Blast.\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63666]Napalm Shell[/url]][u][/u][/b] > This is the reason why healers and ranged must stay 6 yards from each other. The boss will cast it on a random ranged player, and if player Y is close to player X (the victim), he too will take damage from the Shell. \n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63027]Proximity Mine[/url]][u][/u][/b] > These will be spawned around the boss, and if not triggered by players, explode after roughly 30 seconds. One will not kill you, but if you trip over two or three things will go wrong, so be mindful of them.\n\n\n[b][u]Phase 2[/u][/b]:\n\nPhase two starts when Mimiron's Leviathan is defeated. He will now jump to a cannon-like machine, the VX-001. This phase will be pretty hard on your healers, and cannot be tanked, so the tanks should just focus on doing as much damage as they can. To reduce the damage the raid takes we divided the ranged into sub-groups. Group #1 (Warlock, Mage, R-Druid) and Group #2 (Boomkin n' Holy Priest). We decided that the groups should stay 20 yards apart so that only one of them would get hit by the cannon's shots, while moving when necessary due to flames & Laser Barrage. \n\n[ul]\n[li]Abilities:[/li]\n[/ul]\n[u][b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63293]Laser Barrage[/url]][/b][/u] > This ability will normally be cast once or twice during phase two. You can anticipate it by watching the boss [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63414]Spin[/url] and see where his faces his cannons: this attack is frontal cone-only, meaning the raid will need to behind the boss to avoid taking damage, which will result in death. This is this phase's most deadly ability.\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63041]Rocket Strike[/url]][u][/u][/b] You will know where these will land by noticing the [url=http://static.wowhead.com/uploads/screenshots/normal/123628.jpg]red impact circles[/url] on the floor, similar to Hodir's ice. Getting hit by these will generally mean death. \n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=64531]Rapid Burst[/url][u]][/u][/b] > This is why I suggest splitting the ranged into two groups. You will have to eat the damage, but it is also a frontal cone attack, so only one of the sub-groups has to take it.\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63677]Heat Wave[/url][u]][/u][/b] > Raid-wide 'Fire Nova', unavoidable.\n\n\n[b][u]Phase 3[/u][/b]:\n\nPhase three is initiated after the defeat of the VX-001. This time Mimiron will jump to his Aerial Command Unit, which resembles his head. This phase cannot be tanked by melee since the boss is airbourne, meaning a ranged dps will have to tank. To do this, we had a warlock (me) spam [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=47815]Searing Pain[/url] to help build quick threat on the Aerial Unit. It is important for the raid to stay together in this phase so that the fires do not spread too much. Moreover, the tanks need to fast about picking up the adds so the ranged can dps the Aerial Unit with minimal fuss, while the melee destroy the adds. After you destroy the Aerial Unit, you will enter phase 4 We succeeded this way without pulling the 'Head' down.\n\n[ul]\n[li]Abilities:[/li]\n[/ul]\n\n[b][[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63689]Plasma Ball[/url]][u][/u][/b] > This is the Aerial Unit's only attack, and it will be cast on your ranged 'tank'. One healer should be assigned to said tank due to this attack.\n\n[b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=33836#comments]Bomb Bot[/url][/b][b]|[/b][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=34057#comments]Assault Bot[/url][u][/u][/b][b]|[/b][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=33855#comments]Junk Bot[/url][u][/u][/b], all these will spawn during p3 and must quickly be gathered by the tank(s). The most dangerous, the Bomb Bots, must either be killed by ranged or slowed by a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=45524]DK[/url] or a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=42917]Mage[/url].\n \n[b][u]Phase 4[/u][/b]:\n\nPhase 4 is, as you might expect, the hardest. In phase 4, for you will need to deal with all the previous vehicles' abilities when Mimiron unites them to form the V-07-TR-0N. This new robot will have Shock Blast, the Laser Barrage, and the Rockets. To make matters worse, the room will be overrun by fire and you will have little room to work with, not to mention you have an enrage timer to beat. It is now possible to reach this phase with good 4 minutes to spend, although it is unlikely your raid will last 4 minutes in phase 4. Survivability will become a serious issue here, and you must kill the V-07-TR-0N before he kills you. To succeed it is vital that all parts of the robot must die within seconds of each other, or they will repair and you will inevitably wipe. Best of Luck.", "date": "2010-09-12T18:11:39-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you so much for the info on activating hardmode. I've been dredging the comments for a while now trying to figure out how to do this. Never raided during Wrath, so I had no idea, heh. :)", "creationdate": "2017-10-31T13:42:49-05:00", "id": 1082427, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1119471, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Shashos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-09-27T16:46:51-05:00", 3, "Sunlar"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 1344779, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Discobutton", "body": "Thought I should add that this boss is \"Engineerable\" after death, much like many Stone constructs are mineable.\r\n\r\nI did this on 10 man mode, after having killed him after having pushed the big red button. Doing this gave me [item=49050 domain=www]!\r\n\r\nHappy days.", "date": "2011-02-21T12:37:47-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
