{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 1688875, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iroared", "body": "Hardmode is really intense as a death knight. I know it was done quite a while ago, but it's still perhaps the hardest doable boss in ulduar (other than yogg hardmodes).\r\n\r\nI used full DPS gear, with tank 2pc and rings (total 401 iLvl). More tanking gear isn't really needed, maybe except trinkets (mirror would have been decent). 94% of the damage is magical, so mastery is useless - I used a full haste/hit/exp reforge.\r\nPhases 1-3 are nothing serious, Leviathan does quite a bit of damage, but nothing that can't be healed through. Shock blast does ~100k damage, run away unless you have AMS. Plasma blast is what does the damage here. VX-001 is a joke, don't get hit by barrage or rockets, though. Air unit  can be killed in two landings, using all bursts including ERW.\r\n\r\nPhase 4 is by far the hardest, with very high incoming damage (mostly from the damage comes from plasma ball and napalm). The idea is to only hit VX-001 (the middle one), spreading diseases and using heart strike as much as you can without dying from lack of death strikes. The middle unit will die and repair, maybe even twice, depending on DS/HS ratio. When the head is close to dying (under 100k), get a couple death strikes on the Leviathan so it has the same HP, then focus on killing VX-001 again, only using death strikes except for the very end. It repaired twice for me, and I had 20 seconds until the enrage, so watch the timer.", "date": "2012-07-16T17:52:44-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Indeed, really intense, 401 item level as well, full dps gear, could survive till the end, just I couldn't beat the enrage, I was too angry for the previous so close fail to retry again, but had like 20 sec left with the head under 100k, middle unit repaired once, and hit leviathan by mitake and it repaired, making it impossible to beat the self destruct. Should be doable, but really seems to be the hardest hardmode except yogg as you said (actually due to noobishness or rng, I haven't even soloed yogg normal), I soloed all the other hardmodes with even less gear, except thorim (not engineer).", "creationdate": "2012-08-15T12:51:07-05:00", "id": 564042, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1688875, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Esploratore", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 1772221, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "AventuraPL", "body": "Soloed [achievement=3180] as an Affli Warlock with Voidlord/Fel Imp.\r\n\r\n[b]Tactic:[/b]\r\nThe fight consists of four phases - in each phase Mimiron uses some vehicle. Hard Mode is activated by pressing the Big Red Button.\r\n[i]P1 (Leviathan MK II):[/i] You should stay outside the circle of mines, due to Shock Blast. During Napalm Shell your minion will need more healing. Try not to spread the fire throughout the room and not stand in it. Kite the fire like I did on vid.\r\n[i]P2 (VX-001):[/i] Summon Fel Imp instead of Voidlord and do not stand next to him (like me...), otherwise it will die from Rocket Strike. Rocket Strike is deadly and must necessarily be avoided. P3Wx2 Laser Barrage must be avoided too. Try not to spread the fire throughout the room and not stand in it. Kite the fire like I did on vid. In this phase, the fire will be extinguished by Frost Bomb, which should be avoided.\r\n[i]P3 (Aerial Command Unit):[/i] Summon Voidlord instead of Fel Imp. The priority is to destroy all the adds except Emergency Fire Bot. Try to destroy Bomb Bots, before they reach you. You can loot Magnetic Core from Assault Bot and use it underneath Aerial Command Unit in order to disable Mimiron's vehicle, so it will receive an extra dmg. I have not used it, because I like to make life difficult :P Now you can spread the fire throughout the room, because you will have at the disposal firefighters (Emergency Fire Bots), who will extinguish the fire in the room. Remember to stay away from the fire!\r\n[i]P4 (V0-L7R-0N):[/i] Each of the previous vehicles have their own health pool and can be targeted separately. All three targetable sections begin this phase at 50% health and they need to be destroyed within 10 seconds of each other, otherwise they respawn. In this phase, you need to avoid Rocket Strike and P3Wx2 Laser Barrage again. You should also stay outside the circle of mines, due to Shock Blast. You deal with the fire as well as in phase 3.\r\nYou have 10 minutes to complete the encounter. Good Luck and Have Fun!\r\n\r\n[b]Video:[/b]\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b_DpPeEM-j4", "date": "2012-11-30T13:07:27-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
