{"commentv2": 1, "number": 69, "id": 1836097, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kerrymayall", "body": "Blood DK ilvl 490: Phase 4 (10 Man Normal).\n\nPut the head (Aerial Command Unit) of the boss on Focus and keep your Outbreak ticking on the head while spamming Icy Touch as often as you can; the head is out of reach of your melee attacks.  You may periodically need to switch to the middle and lower sections to Death Strike yourself some heals.\n\nOnce the head is below 150-170k health, let your diseases expire and begin dps'ing down the 2 lower sections by using non-disease attacks (so you have greater control over their hitpoints).  Once both of the 2 lower sections are under approximately 80k, summon Army of the Dead, and kill the 2 bottom sections as quickly as you can, use Empower Rune Weapon to replenish your runes, then select the head (which is on Focus) and employ Icy Touch spam to finish the fight before the other sections can repair.", "date": "2013-03-29T04:56:43-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-03-29T04:57:44-05:00", 1, "kerrymayall"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 70, "id": 1856249, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "SaltyPhry", "body": "Just soloed 25 man version as a 491 ret pally.   Quite challenging and very enjoyable at the same time.  15 min enrage coupled with some fairly serious dmg in phases 1 and 4 made for a fine line between dps and survivability.  Most likely if you can survive through the first phase you can probably kill it.  [spell=20925] is a must for talents.  I also found [spell=114154] and [spell=85499] very useful for surviving particularly in phase 1.  Phase 1 is mostly about surviving, the Shock Blast hits for 100k so its best to avoid it, though it wont kill you.  DP can mitigate alot of damage in this phase as well.  Phase 2 and 3 have pretty much no damage so you really want to focus on dps'ing and try to get through as quickly as possible.  I found i could get through phase 3 very quickly if i waited till i had 2 [item=46029], and used AW, GoaK and a mogu pot to burn him down.  If you have less than 5 mins before the enrage going into the last phase you probably wont make it.  Phase 4 is actually easier to survive in then the first phase since you can get alot of self heals by targeting VX-001 and using HotR + SoI.  AW will help burn down the head in this phase, as combo of judgement, exorcism and HoW will bring down it HP fast.  Beyond that its just about keeping yourself alive while getting the other parts below 10%, and trying to have your cd's up for the final burn.  Unless your dps is awesome i don't think you can afford to have any part heal so you have 1 shot to kill all 3 parts.", "date": "2013-05-23T00:14:52-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
