{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 2019125, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "benx2011", "body": "When you die before the chest show even you kill the boss, you can't loot the chest. It just happened to me. I died right after the boss died, but before Mimiron jumped outta the robot. when i rez, the chest was unclickable. I could loot the boss fro junk items, but couldn't loot the chest, couldnt even click it.", "date": "2014-10-25T21:29:58-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-25T21:31:04-05:00", 1, "benx2011"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 2025299, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thalaera", "body": "This fight can be quite difficult for the melee class. You need a ranged ability or two to defeat the head when it's both alone and as a whole for the final phase. You also need to not be standing in the center as phases change or you can be one-shot. On final phase, not sure what but something was one-shotting me every time. I had to have a friend come help.", "date": "2014-11-06T10:41:21-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "UPDATE: I was also getting one-shot...turns out it was from the rocket blast ability in phase 4 (I.e. the huge red targets on the ground...don't stand in them). Although it turns out the hardest part of the fight for me was killing the head as a combat rogue. Imagine running constantly out of range and then spammmmmming 'throw'. Good stuff.", "creationdate": "2014-12-28T20:39:29-06:00", "id": 820038, "rating": 3, "commentid": 2025299, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BluegrassPete", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 2092482, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mystterious", "body": "[b][u]NeEd HeLp PlEaSe ![/u][/b]\r\n\r\nOn mimiron 25 man hard mode, I died a lot on my [b]frost mage item level 666[/b]. I explain why:\r\n\r\nIn phase 4, when you have to attack the head, the body and the tank, Avoid the red circle on the ground if they pop. I did that so I could attack Mimiron [b]all my life[/b] if I wanted to.\r\n\r\nMimiron, in phase 4 got 3 parts\r\n\r\n~ head\r\n~ Body\r\n~ Tank (bottom part)\r\n\r\nSo I killed his head, body and tank. But after I killed everything, he wasnt dead! When I killed the 3 part in this order, tank-body-head, the tank part was alive again after i killed the head. So I killed again the tank part, then the body was alive again... So I killed the body, again, then the head was alive again... It was like that for 10 min, then I abdicated.\r\n\r\nSo what's the order to kill him in phase 4? Is it the head first, the body second and the tank last?\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][u]5 last words:\r\nNeEd HeLp PlEaSe, ThAnK yOu![/u][/b]", "date": "2015-01-21T18:43:09-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Mystterious, there isn't any specific order, but once you 'kill' each part, it goes into a self repair mode. The best thing to do is work on all parts simultaneously and finish each part off as close to the same time as possible, so no part is able to self repair.", "creationdate": "2015-01-22T01:23:00-06:00", "id": 831100, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2092482, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "corilan75", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "OK! I understand, TYVM!", "creationdate": "2015-01-26T16:49:45-06:00", "id": 833003, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2092482, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mystterious", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You have to kill all together otherwise they heal up.", "creationdate": "2015-08-25T14:18:31-05:00", "id": 894406, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2092482, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Khayos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 81, "id": 2099723, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Trickenzie", "body": "For feral druids who wish to solo Mimi (and I would guess other melee classes also) I have found that if, in the last phase, I turn away from him and use my aoes, all parts die at the same time.  This is because my auto attack is not taking down the lower parts faster than the head.  It made the fight rather trivial for me.\r\n\r\nYes, your aoes WILL reach the head.", "date": "2015-02-05T04:15:24-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "http://www.wowhead.com/spell=8921/moonfire and http://www.wowhead.com/spell=5176/wrath", "creationdate": "2015-04-22T01:19:35-05:00", "id": 864586, "rating": -5, "commentid": 2099723, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "wonderbrah", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 2111619, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "paiway", "body": "Warriors may find him frustrating to solo, especially Firefighter 25. Respec Protection for the Thunderclap bleed and no cooldown on Heroic Throw and you should have no problems bringing the head down in time before the enrage.", "date": "2015-02-19T20:45:47-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 83, "id": 2254771, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mystterious", "body": "If you die on Mimiron, it is because of 1 ability named [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=63041/rocket-strike]Rocket Strike[/url]. This chit does 5 millions of fire damage so it kills you instantly. So you should click the link in this comment and also check the screenshots of this, to see what it look like. After you'll be ready to avoid this chit, during the fight.\r\n\r\nHave a nice day,\r\nGood luck!", "date": "2015-09-21T01:32:03-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Doesn't hit for anywhere near 5Mil. Hits a level 100 Rogue for about 100k though.", "creationdate": "2016-01-09T02:13:07-06:00", "id": 923798, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2254771, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tuckletuts", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 84, "id": 2360305, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Limelols", "body": "For Melee classes, during his flying phase, there's an item you can loot off the mobs that spawn that brings him down to the ground.\r\n\r\nDuring the final phase, when you're fighting all 3 at once, it should be noted that the flying part is closer to the ground than before. Any melee ability with an 8 yard range (Whirlwind for example) will hit it, so don't waste your time just using Heroic throws.", "date": "2016-08-02T03:15:14-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As a warrior, just spam whirlwind to kill all three parts simultaneously.", "creationdate": "2016-08-22T17:41:56-05:00", "id": 962519, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2360305, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Waterfuzz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "bugged since 7.1 the item WONT bring him down and he not reachable by anything beside heroic trow anymore for my war.....", "creationdate": "2016-11-01T16:28:56-05:00", "id": 1004111, "rating": 8, "commentid": 2360305, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "robbiedehand", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "In P4, try jumping up and then use Dragon Roar. Works for me :)", "creationdate": "2016-11-19T16:34:39-06:00", "id": 1010221, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2360305, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "redfoxert", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "At the moment of typing this, it looks like the magnetic core _won't_ pull the aerial command unit down to melee range _unless_ you first pull the command unit away from the middle.", "creationdate": "2017-01-26T06:44:45-06:00", "id": 1028161, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2360305, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Philander", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I know its not the best solution, but if you run to the edges of the room the Unit will follow you and it should be in range then. gl!", "creationdate": "2017-03-21T12:29:18-05:00", "id": 1038465, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2360305, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mutsumi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 2361055, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Demiona", "body": "This boss is significantly easier if you bring some ranged dps with you. It's possible to solo as a melee, but you save yourself a lot of trouble if you don't. The last phase requires you to get all parts down at once, which as a melee is tricky as you're entirely reliant on the items that drop from the adds during the encounter.", "date": "2016-08-03T11:56:45-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 2441214, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zebix", "body": "Funny thing: at level 100+, you out-heal the self-destruction explosion.\r\n\r\nSo as long as you have a weak range attack, you can kill Mimiron hardmode, it can take ages, but it works eventually, I got the achiev on my alt so I'm sure the hardmode kill was validated with the self-destruction explosion ongoing since the Aerial phase! :)", "date": "2016-11-06T15:07:48-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 87, "id": 2461901, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jeolene", "body": "This will probably never be noticed, but I just realized today, the different mechs are named:\r\n\r\nxt-002\r\nvx-001\r\nAerial command unit\r\n\r\nThere is no way any of that forms the name:\r\n\r\nV-07-TR-0N", "date": "2017-01-11T16:22:03-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 88, "id": 2479164, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "MetalMinx", "body": "So is it just me or is this guy bugged since a while back?\r\n\r\nWhenever he switches to the flying phase, there's two problems.\r\n\r\n1. I can't target him even with ranged attacks, using Pistol Shot on my Rogue keeps giving me the \"out of range\" message, no matter where I stand.\r\n2. The item that drops off of one of the adds no longer makes the boss drop to the ground.\r\n\r\nI've still managed to kill him, though. I jump back and forth beneath him, and spam a few attacks. Every now and then one attack manages to hit him, and luckily you do so much damage to him at level 110 that he dies in one or two hits.\r\n\r\nStill, really annoying as it makes the fight longer than it needs to be. I already found it annoying to have to wait in between the phases..\r\n\r\nAm I the only one with this problem?", "date": "2017-03-23T18:14:46-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "i have those problems too", "creationdate": "2017-04-15T05:33:32-05:00", "id": 1045246, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2479164, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "emmaworld", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
